{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Quick Start\n",
    "Hereâ€™s a basic example of how to use **pyramid-learn**, or **midlearn**, to explain a trained LightGBM model, utilizing the familiar scikit-learn API."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import fetch_california_housing\n",
    "from sklearn import set_config\n",
    "\n",
    "import lightgbm as lgb\n",
    "import midlearn as mid \n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up plotnine theme for clean visualizations\n",
    "import plotnine as p9\n",
    "p9.theme_set(p9.theme_bw(base_family='Serif'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configure scikit-learn display\n",
    "set_config(display='text')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Train a Black-Box Model\n",
    "We use the California Housing dataset to train a LightGBM Regressor, which will serve as our black-box model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[LightGBM] [Info] Auto-choosing col-wise multi-threading, the overhead of testing was 0.000253 seconds.\n",
      "You can set `force_col_wise=true` to remove the overhead.\n",
      "[LightGBM] [Info] Total Bins 1838\n",
      "[LightGBM] [Info] Number of data points in the train set: 15480, number of used features: 8\n",
      "[LightGBM] [Info] Start training from score 2.070349\n",
      "LGBMRegressor(random_state=42)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Load and prepare data\n",
    "housing = fetch_california_housing()\n",
    "X = pd.DataFrame(housing.data, columns=housing.feature_names)\n",
    "y = housing.target\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit a LightGBM regression model\n",
    "estimator = lgb.LGBMRegressor(random_state=42)\n",
    "estimator.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(estimator)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Create an Explaination Model\n",
    "We fit the `MIDExplainer` to the training data to create a globally faithful, interpretable surrogate model (MID)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Generating predictions from the estimator...\n",
      "MIDExplainer(estimator=LGBMRegressor(random_state=42), params_main=100,\n",
      "             penalty=0.05)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize and fit the MID model\n",
    "explainer = mid.MIDExplainer(\n",
    "    estimator=estimator,\n",
    "    interaction=True,\n",
    "    params_main=100,\n",
    "    penalty=.05,\n",
    "    singular_ok=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "explainer.fit(X_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(explainer)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 50,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Generating predictions from the estimator...\n",
      "R-squared score: 0.9493631147465892\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Check the fidelity of the surrogate model to the original model\n",
    "print(\"R-squared score:\", explainer.fidelity_score(X_test))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize the fidelity\n",
    "p = p9.ggplot() \\\n",
    "    + p9.geom_abline(slope=1, color='gray') \\\n",
    "    + p9.geom_point(p9.aes(estimator.predict(X_test), explainer.predict(X_test)), alpha=0.5, shape=\".\") \\\n",
    "    + p9.labs(\n",
    "        x='Prediction (LightGBM Regressor)',\n",
    "        y='Prediction (Surrogate MID Regressor)',\n",
    "        title='Surrogate Model Fidelity Check'\n",
    "    )\n",
    "p"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Visualize the Explanation Model\n",
    "The MID model allows for clear visualization of feature importance, individual effects, and local prediction breakdowns."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 121,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate and plot overall feature importance (default bar plot and heatmap)\n",
    "imp = explainer.importance()\n",
    "display(\n",
    "    imp.plot(\n",
    "        max_nterms=20\n",
    "    ) +\n",
    "    p9.ggtitle(\"Importance Plot\")\n",
    ")\n",
    "display(\n",
    "    imp.plot(\n",
    "        style='heatmap'\n",
    "    ) +\n",
    "    p9.ggtitle(\"Importance Heatmap\")\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 52,

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Plot the top 3 important main effects (Component Functions)\n",
    "for i, t in enumerate(imp.terms(interactions=False)[:3]):\n",
    "    p = (\n",
    "        explainer.plot(term=t) +\n",
    "        p9.ggtitle(f\"Main Effect of {t}\")\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    display(p)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Plot the interaction of Longitude and Latitude (Component Functions)\n",
    "display(\n",
    "    explainer.plot(\n",
    "        \"Longitude:Latitude\",\n",
    "        main_effects=True\n",
    "    ) +\n",
    "    p9.ggtitle(\"Total Effect of Longitude and Latitude\")\n",
    ")\n",
    "display(\n",
    "    explainer.plot(\n",
    "        \"Longitude:Latitude\",\n",
    "        style='data',\n",
    "        theme='mako',\n",
    "        data=X_train,\n",
    "        main_effects=True\n",
    "    ) +\n",
    "    p9.ggtitle(\"Total Effect of Longitude and Latitude\")\n",
    "\n",
    ")"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Plot prediction breakdowns for the first three test samples (Local Interpretability)\n",
    "for i in range(3):\n",
    "    p = (\n",
    "        explainer.breakdown(row=i, data=X_test).plot() +\n",
    "        p9.ggtitle(f\"Breakdown Plot for Row ({i})\")\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    display(p)"
   ]

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Plot individual conditional expectations (ICE) with color encoding\n",
    "ice = explainer.conditional(\n",
    "    variable='MedInc',\n",
    "    data=X_train.head(500)\n",
    ")\n",
    "display(\n",
    "    ice.plot(alpha=.1) +\n",
    "    p9.ggtitle(\"ICE Plot of MedInc\")\n",
    ")\n",
    "display(\n",
    "    ice.plot(\n",
    "        style='centered',\n",
    "        var_color='HouseAge',\n",
    "        theme='mako'\n",
    "    ) +\n",
    "    p9.ggtitle(\"Centered ICE Plot of MedInc\")\n",
    ")"
